The paper deals with video analysis and recognition using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of LSTM networks for temporal modeling and prediction also suggests a possible fit in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on laparoscopic surgeries, which are a type of medical imaging and could potentially be classified under multimedia (cs.MM) or robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
